    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-cou1-decision",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2. Validation results demonstrate adequate agreement with experimental benchmark data across the CPB operating envelope. RH < 1 acceptance criterion satisfied at all tested operating conditions. The assessment team notes that aleatory uncertainty in the velocity field validation result was characterized qualitatively rather than through a structured UQ method; this was judged acceptable given the low sensitivity of the hemolysis QoI to velocity field variability at MRL 2. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory decision.",
